                <text type="warning_phenomena">Warning to Sheep Graziers</text>
                <text type="warning_areas">Mount Lofty Ranges, Lower Eyre Peninsula, Yorke Peninsula, Kangaroo Island, Flinders and Lower South East forecast districts</text>
                <text type="warning">Sheep graziers are warned that cold temperatures, rain and showers and strong westerly winds are expected during Thursday. Areas likely to be affected include the Mount Lofty Ranges forecast district and parts of the Lower Eyre Peninsula, Yorke Peninsula, Kangaroo Island, Flinders and Lower South East forecast districts. There is a risk of losses of lambs and sheep exposed to these conditions.</text>
